n?<\/span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"eb\">Justification<\/span> is used to talk about finding or understanding reasons for actions, or trying to explain why it is a good idea to do something. It is often used with words like <span class=\"ei\">little<\/span>, <span class=\"ei\">no<\/span>, <span class=\"ei\">some<\/span>, <span class=\"ei\">every<\/span>, <span class=\"ei\">without<\/span>, and <span class=\"ei\">not any<\/span>. <span class=\"eb\">Grounds<\/span> is used more for talking about reasons that already exist, or that have already been decided, for example by law: <span class=\"ei\">moral\/economic grounds<\/span>.<\/span><\/div><ul class=\"deflist\"><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"dt\">pretext<\/span> <span class=\"dd\">(<span class=\"ei\">rather formal<\/span>) a false reason that you give for doing something, usually something bad, in order to hide the real reason:<ul class=\"eg\"><li><span class=\"unx\">He left the party early on the pretext of having to work.<\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/li><\/ul><span class=\"patterns\">Patterns<\/span><ul class=\"bullet\"><li class=\"li\">(a\/an) reason\/explanation\/grounds\/basis\/excuse\/motive\/justification\/pretext <span class=\"eb\">for<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\">the reason\/motive <span class=\"eb\">behind<\/span> something<\/li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"eb\">on the<\/span> grounds\/basis\/pretext <span class=\"eb\">of\/that\u2026<\/span><\/li><li class=\"li\">(a) <span class=\"eb\">good\/valid<\/span> reason\/explanation\/grounds\/excuse\/motive\/justification<\/li><\/ul><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><h2 class=\"h2\">in liquid<\/h2><div class=\"d1\"><div class=\"d2\"><h3 class=\"h3\"><span class=\"sensetop\"><div class=\"variants\" type=\"alt\"><span class=\"v-g\"><span class=\"v\">grounds<\/span><\/span><\/div><\/span><span class=\"gr\">[plural]<\/span><span class=\"def\">the small pieces of solid matter in a liquid that have fallen to the bottom<\/span><\/h3><div class=\"d5\